        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 4:43PM MDT by NWS North Platte NE</headline>
        <description>At 443 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 15 miles southeast of Gordon, moving northeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Intersection of Highway 61 and Shadbolt Road, Intersection of Highway
20 and Irwin Road, Rock Hill, Bayonne, and Highway 27 crossing the
Niobrara River.

This includes the following highways...
Highway 20 between mile markers 107 and 123.
Highway 61 between mile markers 207 and 216.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
